thread.title: Royals work out in advance of World Series
thread.title_full: Royals work out in advance of World Series - KCTV5

author: Dave Eckert, Assignment Editor
title: Royals work out in advance of World Series
text:
KANSAS CITY, MO (KCTV) - The Royals were back on the field at Kauffman Stadium Sunday.
For the first time since the team's Champagne-soaked clinching win in the American League Championship Series Friday night, the Royals returned to the K for some work in the batting cage.
The Royals opponents, of course, are the New York Mets, no strangers to the series. This is the Mets fifth appearance in The Fall Classic
Their strong starting pitching is mainly credited with winning the Mets a spot in the series.
Manager Ned Yost says facing the Mets starters will be tough.
"Their top three guys could be number one guys in any organization," Yost said. "I told my guys just play your game. We do what we do."
Game one of the World Series is Tuesday night out at Kauffman Stadium. First pitch is set for 7:07 p.m..
